      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900">How to Find Legitimate Remote Jobs: Platforms, Red Flags, and Tips</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-600">The remote job market is full of opportunity — and scams. Here is how to find legitimate remote positions, avoid the fakes, and increase your chances of landing the right role.</p>

      <div class="mt-10 prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-none">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-6 not-prose">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-800">The Reality Check</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-red-700">Remote job scams have increased 300% since 2020. Common scams include: fake job listings that collect personal information, "pay for training" schemes, check-cashing scams disguised as equipment stipends, and multi-level marketing operations pretending to be remote jobs. Knowing the red flags is as important as knowing where to look.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>The Best Remote Job Platforms</h2>
        <p>Different platforms work better for different industries and experience levels. For a detailed side-by-side comparison with pros, cons, and salary ranges, use our <a href="/tools/remote-job-finder/">Remote Job Finder tool</a>. Here are the highlights:</p>

        <h3>LinkedIn — Best for All Industries</h3>
        <p>The largest professional network with the most remote job listings. Use the "Remote" location filter. Set up job alerts for your target role + "remote." The "Easy Apply" option lets you apply in seconds, but a tailored application always works better.</p>

        <h3>FlexJobs — Best for Scam-Free Browsing</h3>
        <p>Every listing is hand-screened before publication. You will never find a scam on FlexJobs. The downside: it costs $2.95/week to apply. But for many job seekers, the time saved avoiding scams is worth the small fee.</p>

        <h3>We Work Remotely — Best for Tech Roles</h3>
        <p>One of the oldest remote-only job boards. All listings are guaranteed remote. The quality of postings is high because it costs employers $299 to post. Heavy on tech, design, and marketing roles.</p>

        <h3>Wellfound (AngelList) — Best for Startups</h3>
        <p>Transparent salary and equity information. Direct communication with founders and hiring managers. Best for tech, product, and design roles at startups.</p>

        <h2>Red Flags: How to Spot a Remote Job Scam</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>They ask for money upfront.</strong> Legitimate employers never charge you to apply, for training, or for equipment. Never.</li>
          <li><strong>The salary is unrealistically high.</strong> "$80/hour for data entry, no experience needed" — it is a scam. Always.</li>
          <li><strong>Poor communication.</strong> Emails from Gmail addresses (not company domain), messages full of typos, vague job descriptions.</li>
          <li><strong>They send you a check.</strong> The "employer" sends a check to buy equipment, asks you to deposit it and send back the excess. The check bounces. You lose the money. This is the most common remote job scam.</li>
          <li><strong>Interview via text chat only.</strong> Legitimate companies do video or phone interviews. Text-only = scam.</li>
          <li><strong>They ask for sensitive personal info too early.</strong> Your SSN, bank details, or passport scan should only come after a formal job offer — never during the initial application.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Tips to Actually Get Hired</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Tailor every application.</strong> Generic applications are easy to spot and almost never get interviews.</li>
          <li><strong>Highlight remote work skills.</strong> Self-discipline, written communication, time management, familiarity with remote tools. These matter as much as technical skills.</li>
          <li><strong>Set up a professional video call background.</strong> Good lighting, clean background, quality audio. First impressions happen through your webcam now.</li>
          <li><strong>Apply quickly.</strong> Remote job listings get 2-3x more applications than in-office roles. Set up alerts and apply within 24-48 hours of posting.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Ready to start searching? Use our <a href="/tools/remote-job-finder/">Remote Job Finder</a> to compare the best platforms for your industry and experience level.</p>
